title: Elon Musk Wants to Challenge Google and Microsoft in AI
description: Twitter boss tells WSJ London event the social-media company could be cash-flow positive starting in June.

title: Ron DeSantis to Launch 2024 Presidential Run in Twitter Talk With Elon Musk
description: The billionaire opened The Wall Street Journal’s CEO Council Summit in London. He was expected to face questions about his efforts to turn around Twitter, stoke demand for Teslas and advance SpaceX’s program.

title: Biden Administration Developing National AI Strategy
description: The White House is seeking public input on rules for new artificial intelligence tools such as ChatGPT.

title: Social Media Could Pose 'Profound Risk of Harm' to Young People's Mental Health, Surgeon General Warns
description: The advisory notes the benefits of the platforms, but urges action to limit any detrimental effects.

title: Apple Strikes Multibillion-Dollar Supply Deal With Broadcom
description: Apple has entered a multiyear deal with the chip and network equipment maker for components that will be made in the U.S.

title: Meta Agrees to Sell Giphy on Regulator's Order
description: Shutterstock said it agreed to buy Giphy for $53 million in net cash, giving it a mobile content platform with 1.7 billion daily users.

title: Elon Musk to Join WSJ's CEO Council Summit to Talk Tesla, Twitter, SpaceX and More
description: Speakers following Musk include Treasury Secretary Janet Yellen, Bank of England Gov. Andrew Bailey and former Google CEO Eric Schmidt.
